      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add your<strong> toasted sesame oil </strong>and heat for 1-2 min or until very hot, then carefully pour the <strong>heated toasted sesame oil </strong>into the bowl,<strong> </strong>give it a good mix up and set aside for later (save the pan!) – this is your <strong>chilli oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Be careful – the garlic and ginger will sizzle from the heat of the oil!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1620663357264-x200.jpg",
